# Node version sync with CI

This project pins the Node version for local dev in **`.nvmrc`** and **`.node-version`** so `nvm use` / `fnm use` match CI.

**When you change the Node version in any workflow** (e.g. `node-version:` in `.github/workflows/ci.yml` or `actions/setup-node`):

1. Update **`.nvmrc`** to the same version (e.g. `22` or `20`).
2. Update **`.node-version`** to the same value.

Use the same format in both files (e.g. `22` for current LTS major, or `22.0.0` for an exact version). This keeps local dev and CI aligned.
